column5: Hey guys,

Nice!   I always wanted to fish out of there in autumn.    I spent a week in the summer fishing there and it was so busy I hated it.    However, there were so many areas that looked amazing for pike fishing that I really wanted to head back in autumn.   Good to see a report from there.
Not sure why you would bother to post pics with your faces covered...Kinda ruins the whole sharing pics thing IMO
To be honest when you're holding a fish, nobody is looking at your face anyway.  Nice fish by the way!
Not sure why you would bother to post pics with your faces covered...Kinda ruins the whole sharing pics thing IMO X2... You on the wanted list ??  Nice fish though..
When I first started posting here I blocked out my face.   Then I realized OFC accepts my ugly mug.  Or maybe they dont? I just post it anyways???  Howd that musky taste???
PAB is a wonderful spot, especially in the fall. Good report. I saw your face at the Canadian Customs Border crossing at Queenston a few weeks ago. Your secret is safe.

Geez and I thought I might have been picking on him a bit much in his introduction thread.  Maybe he doesn't need his face recognized for reasons we don't know and he doesn't feel a need to discuss it.  Perhaps he's just shy.  Who knows and who cares?  I sure don't. Nice catch!  I think it's the IMG code you need to paste in from photobucket to get the pictures to appear, as I said before it's been a while. Keep 'em coming!  Michael

nice and congrat's on the catches When I first started posting here I blocked out my face.Then I realized OFC accepts my ugly mug.Or maybe they dont? I just post it anywaysHowd that musky taste??? like chicken
The ones I keep taste like poor mans lobster???
Weird????  The ones I keep taste like poor mans lobster All the one's I keep taste like rich man's pike....   :rofl2:
Not sure why you would bother to post pics with your faces covered...Kinda ruins the whole sharing pics thing IMO  Well some do,some dont. Who cares.  Nice fish.
Well some do,some dont. Who cares.  Nice fish.   LOL !!!!!
Epic???

Too funny Brian!  Mine sinuses is burning from the pepsi that I just shot all over my monitor.  Oh well, guess it (and my sinuses) needed a good cleaning anyways!  (any secrets for stopping the burning?)  Betcha Musky Plug's next post will copy your idea!  Michael

Nice!   I always wanted to fish out of there in autumn.    I spent a week in the summer fishing there and it was so busy I hated it.    However, there were so many areas that looked amazing for pike fishing that I really wanted to head back in autumn.   Good to see a report from there.   Summer time there is busy with traffic, but as soon as labour day comes it drops right off. There were hardly any boats out when we were there.  Geez and I thought I might have been picking on him a bit much in his introduction thread.  Maybe he doesn't need his face recognized for reasons we don't know and he doesn't feel a need to discuss it.  Perhaps he's just shy.  Who knows and who cares?  I sure don't. Nice catch!  I think it's the IMG code you need to paste in from photobucket to get the pictures to appear, as I said before it's been a while. Keep 'em coming!  Michael   Just personal preference, will change eventually. Thanks dude.   Well some do,some dont. Who cares.  Nice fish.    Lmao. I cried.
Well some do,some dont. Who cares.  Nice fish.    What a nice guy! No reason to embarrass the fish!
Well some do,some dont. Who cares.  Nice fish.    OMG, is there an award we can give this guy????  That was beyond awesome...
You guys got too much time on your hands!  LOL!  I love it.
lol Brian!!!!!! HH
the dream is alive...still havent boated a musky in PAB  we shall talk.  nice catches by the way.
